<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="700" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,760,650,929]" pageId="33" pageNumber="700">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,682,705]" pageId="33" pageNumber="700">Remarks.</emphasis>
Unfortunately, the abovementioned specimen was destroyed during the fire in MNRJ. Nevertheless, I feel it is important to mention it as it is not only a new record for the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[305,411,778,801]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="33" pageNumber="700">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
but also the first accurately labelled specimen of this species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1859" box="[486,602,810,833]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oediopalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="700" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvipes">
<emphasis box="[486,602,810,833]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="700">O. fulvipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described generally from 
<collectingCountry box="[315,384,842,865]" name="Brazil" pageId="33" pageNumber="700">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. It represented a very characteristic species, and the specimen perfectly matched the 
<typeStatus box="[666,759,874,897]" pageId="33" pageNumber="700">holotype</typeStatus>
which I compared it to back in 2017.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
